  "cluster_information": {
    "cluster_id": "0x0004",
    "name": "Groups",
    "description": "The Groups cluster manages, per endpoint, the content of the node-wide Group Table that is part of the underlying interaction layer. In a network supporting fabrics, group IDs referenced by attributes or other elements of this cluster are scoped to the accessing fabric. The Groups cluster is scoped to the endpoint. Groups cluster commands support discovering the endpoint membership in a group, adding the endpoint to a group, removing the endpoint from a group, removing endpoint membership from all groups. All commands defined in this cluster SHALL only affect groups scoped to the accessing fabric."
  },
